{"content": "\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">General Purpose (Permissionless)</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th>Blockchain</th><th>Pros</th><th>Cons</th><th>Focus</th><th>Partners</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Ethereum</td><td>Deep liquidity; composable</td><td>High fees; fragmented</td><td>Funds; credit</td><td>BlackRock; Franklin Templeton; J.P. Morgan</td></tr><tr><td>Solana</td><td>Fast; low cost</td><td>Outage history; infra-heavy</td><td>Stablecoins; funds</td><td>PayPal; Visa; Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 G\u00e9n\u00e9rale</td></tr><tr><td>Avalanche</td><td>Compliant subnets</td><td>Split liquidity; complex ops</td><td>Venues; private markets</td><td>Citi; KKR; T. Rowe Price</td></tr><tr><td>Polygon</td><td>Cheap EVM; pilot-ready</td><td>Not rollup; L2 competition</td><td>Bonds; fund pilots</td><td>Mastercard; Siemens; Hamilton Lane</td></tr><tr><td>Aptos</td><td>Move safety; fast</td><td>New; thinner liquidity</td><td>Fund shares; RWA trading</td><td>BlackRock; Franklin Templeton; Ondo</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Utility &amp; Settlement (Permissionless)</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th>Blockchain</th><th>Pros</th><th>Cons</th><th>Focus</th><th>Partners</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Tron</td><td>USDT scale; low cost</td><td>Limited securities fit</td><td>Stablecoin rails</td><td>Tether; Binance</td></tr><tr><td>Stellar</td><td>Payment rails; issuance</td><td>Smaller DeFi; newer contracts</td><td>Remittance; cash tokens</td><td>WisdomTree; IBM; MoneyGram</td></tr><tr><td>XRP</td><td>FX routing; stability</td><td>Ripple optics; narrower DeFi</td><td>Payments; stablecoins</td><td>Ripple; Santander; Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 G\u00e9n\u00e9rale</td></tr><tr><td>Hedera</td><td>Enterprise governance</td><td>Limited DeFi depth</td><td>Tokenized funds; settlement</td><td>State Street; Archax; abrdn</td></tr><tr><td>Algorand</td><td>Instant finality; controls</td><td>Non-EVM; low liquidity</td><td>Regulated cash; DvP</td><td>Quantoz; Archax</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">RWA Specialized (Permissionless)</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th>Blockchain</th><th>Pros</th><th>Cons</th><th>Focus</th><th>Partners</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Provenance</td><td>Loan lifecycle</td><td>Concentrated ecosystem</td><td>Loans; securitization</td><td>Figure; Apollo; J.P. Morgan</td></tr><tr><td>XDC</td><td>Trade finance</td><td>Niche adoption</td><td>Trade docs; receivables</td><td>SBI; International Chamber of Commerce; Federated Hermes</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Institution Network (Permissioned)</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th>Blockchain</th><th>Pros</th><th>Cons</th><th>Focus</th><th>Partners</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Canton</td><td>Privacy network</td><td>No public liquidity</td><td>Repo; collateral</td><td>Goldman Sachs; BNP Paribas; Citi</td></tr><tr><td>Kinexys (J.P. Morgan)</td><td>Bank-grade ops</td><td>Closed network</td><td>Collateral; intraday</td><td>J.P. Morgan; BlackRock; Barclays</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n", "img": "https://picsum.photos/seed/blockchains-for-capital-markets-2026-direction/800/400", "date": "2025-12-26", "excerpt": "A comparative overview of leading blockchains used in capital markets, covering general-purpose, settlement, RWA-focused, and permissioned institutional network", "title": "Blockchains for Capital Markets 2026 Direction", "slug": "blockchains-for-capital-markets-2026-direction"}